That's really cool mate, I appreciate the hard work. Now for what's left : 

1. Position read/write is just a bit of bit magic. If I understand this correctly
```javascript
function readPos(buf) {
  var posNum = buf.readInt64();
  var x = posNum >> 38;
  var y = (posNum >> 26) & 0xFFF;
  var z = (posNum << 38) >> 38;
  return {x: x, y: y, z: z};
}
function writePos(value, buf) {
  buf.writeInt64(((value.x & 0x3FFFFFF) << 38) | ((value.y & 0xFFF) << 26) | (value.z & 0x3FFFFFF));
}
```
Or something like that, anyway.

2. map_chunk_bulk... URG. Why the hell did they not send a goddamn size ?! I have a clever hack for this one, but it's too late at night for this one right now, so I'll see aobut it tomorrow. 

3. For world_particles, that's easy
```javascript
world_particles: {id: 0x2a, fields: [
  { name: "particleId", type: "int" },
  { name: "longDistance", type: "bool"},
  { name: "x", type: "float" },
  { name: "y", type: "float" },
  { name: "z", type: "float" },
  { name: "offsetX", type: "float" },
  { name: "offsetY", type: "float" },
  { name: "offsetZ", type: "float" },
  { name: "particleData", type: "float" },
  { name: "particles", type: "count", typeArgs: { countFor: "data", type: "int" }},
  { name: "data", type: "array", typeArgs: { type: "varint", count: "particles" }}
]},
```

4. seems relatively straightforward, but will need a tiny bit of reworking the internals. I'll think about it tomorrow.

5. So this one is going to need heavy use of conditionals. Urg. take a look at https://github.com/wtfaremyinitials/node-minecraft-protocol/blob/packets-1.8/lib/protocol.js#L486 for how conditional support works. I'll create the implementation tomorrow.

6. NBTTags. Urgs. This one is going to abuse the same clever hack I'll use for maps (take the rest of the content from the packet, and feed it in an array)

